    </introduction>

    <task>
      <statement>
        <p>
          Explain why the above equality is equivalent to <me>x_i+\sum_j \lfloor a_{ij} \rfloor x_j - \lfloor b_i\rfloor =(b_i - \lfloor b_i \rfloor) - \sum_j (a_{ij} - \lfloor a_{ij} \rfloor)x_j </me>
        </p>
      </statement>
    </task>

    <task>
      <statement>
        <p>
          Show that for any feasible  integral solution,  that the left hand side of the equality in <m>\textbf{(a)}</m> is an integer.
        </p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task>
      <statement>
        <p>
          Show that the right hand side of the equation in <m>\textbf{(a)}</m> is strictly less than 1 for any feasible solution.
        </p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task>
      <statement>
        <p>
          For any integral solution, what is a nonnegative integer upper bound for 
          <m>(b_i - \lfloor b_i \rfloor) - \sum_j (a_{ij} - \lfloor a_{ij} \rfloor)x_j</m>?
        </p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task>
      <statement>
        <p>
          Show that 
          <me>  \sum_j (\lfloor a_{ij} \rfloor - a_{ij})x_j \leq (\lfloor b_i \rfloor - b_i)</me>
          for any feasible integral solution to the relaxation of the integer optimization problem.
        </p>
        <p>
          We call the hyperplane <m>\sum_j (\lfloor a_{ij} \rfloor - a_{ij})x_j = (\lfloor b_i \rfloor - b_i)</m>
          a <em>cutting-plane</em>.
        </p>
      </statement>
    </task>
    <task>
      <statement>
        <p>
          Show that if <m>b_i</m> is nonintegral, then by adding this constraint, the solution <m>x_1^*, \ldots, x_m^*, \ldots, x_{m+n}^*</m> is no longer feasible.
        </p>
      </statement>
    </task>
